items.name: Head Size Slider
items.description:
In order to not violate TOS by putting images of minors, I will only upload modified images for the showcase.

This model is trained on a custom merged model, extracted negative concept from big head doll, the other side of 'big head' is 'big body' along with other prompts to strength the positive concept(I am not sure if it is obvious or not, I couldn't use 'small head' to excite the positive concept as it has 'head' in its substring and create bigger head than normal).

  1. This is not an age slider, so you can get bigger head than a normal person.

  2. Well, this basically do not work with controlnet, so only use for slight adjustment is recommended. Define your background is also recommended.

  3. Recommended weight: -5 to +5 (depends on what model you are using, you can always go higher if you want to try).

  4. Add in positive prompts: 'detailed, intricate' and in negative prompts: 'deformed iris, deformed pupil, blurry' to have better big heads.

  5. positive for smaller head, bigger body

  6. negative for bigger head, small body

  7. Perhaps you can buy me a beer if you enjoy the models and want to help me motivatedüò∫

    https://ko-fi.com/nextmealslider

items.name: SDXL Artstyle Grab-Bag #1 -  ("Triangle Glass Houses")
items.description:
I'm just getting started w/ the switch to SDXL, so I've decided to start a series of these attempts for anyone bored or who might enjoy a "hit or miss" LoRA that could spice up an otherwise normalish prompt/generation. Take em or leave em - no guarantees :)

One thing I always loved doing w/ v1.5 and Dreambooth was to throw a small batch of random images from surfing various social media sites in a folder, and seeing how they trained out. After generating images overnight w/ those models I'd pick some good ones and use them in another training session - and so on. Sharing some of those interesting (but not necessarily definable or specific) mish-mash models is what I plan on sharing in this "SDXL Artstyle Grab-Bag" series.

#1 - "Triangle Modern Houses" - Trigger with "trhs artstyle"

Trained on 12 images of modern glass/triangle cabins/houses mostly in the woods. You'll likely need to play w/ the LoRA weighting to find a good balance. Entering the prompt alone will give you a good idea of the training set - throwing the LoRA on a random prompt could give it a style edge and maybe turn out interesting. Post if you enjoy your results!

items.name: 4th WALL BREAKER - 4 Styles Combo Lora üè¥‚Äç‚ò†Ô∏èDOKA Piratesüè¥‚Äç‚ò†Ô∏è
items.description:
Hey there, if you're creating tons of pictures daily for family and clients, this type of LORA could be your new friend.

I want to speed up my workflow and also test SDXL‚Äôs limit so I decide to train 4 DIFFERENT ART STYLES using only 1 LORA, and to push it further I mashed them all into a single 1 collage picture. Which mean this LORA could rock 4 different Art Styles in just 1 image.

SETTINGS

  • WEIGHT: 0.8-1 to make a collage of 4 images. Or 0.4-0.7 to blend all 4 styles which will give birth to the 5th original style. (Image 10, 11, 15 & 17)

  • FOCUS: It's trained to draw PORTRAIT (human) - my primary use case. If there's demand, I'll expand this Lora's capabilities to include full body, animals, landscapes, etc.

  • PROMPT: You can allow it to draw freely (5th image), or for greater similarity among the four images, include specific description (white hair, pink crop top, etc.)

  • OTHER: Compatible with Auto1111 default setting, let me know if you got good results with other settings

  • TRIGGER WORD: 4WBK (optional)

MY MAIN GOALS:

  1. SAVE MOTHER EARTH: Also cut my bill & spare my old GPU

  2. 4X FASTER BRAINSTORMING PROCESS: No 1024x1024 needed during brainstorming, Quadruple the speed is more appetizing.

  3. SIMPLIFY TESTING PROCESS: Skip XYZ setup & repetitive style name typing. Plus keep a XYZ slot free for other purposes

  4. DESTROY THE WALL BETWEEN REALITY & ART STYLES: Mix it with a REAL FACE LORA & enjoy (may work with Character Loras if they could draw portrait). Also I don‚Äôt like it when some LORA doesn‚Äôt draw male or other things well so using Combo Style LORA may help with that.

  5. CREATE NEW ART STYLE: An unexpected bonus I found out after training >> Setting weight at 0.4-0.7 could blend all 4 styles which will give birth to the 5th original style.

  6. INPAINTING: I got some very interesting results. However, the result is a bit random due to the fact that SDXL is not an inpainting-focus model and this LORA only train on 28 images. I expected that we could solve this with more training

I only have enough time to create 112 close-up portraits for training. I'm not sure, but I think it needs at least 400 images to establish a stable connection between 4 styles (full body, animals, architecture, etc.).

FUTURE PLANS:

  • If there's enough interest, I'll generate more training data and retrain the model.

  • If you need it, I can also create four Lora models for the four styles I used here.

  • In the future, I might increase the total number of styles to test the limit of SDXL

If you like it please:

  • Upload your images on CivitAI so I can join the tournament too. There is only a few days left and I need 50 images from you guys to join.

  • Give me suggestions to further enhance this Lora. You con comment here or DM my Discord

  • Or buy me a coffee on Ko-fi or Patreon

Again, this is just the first version, I hope more people will enjoy this & we'll see more LORAs of this type down the road.

Cheers!

2023.8.24 9:22: Something wrong with export script, the fixed models have been re-uploaded, now the models are well-tested.

NOTE: The associated trigger words are only for reference, it may need to be adjusted at some times.

How to Use This Model

USE THEM SIMULTANEOUSLY. In this case, you need to download both magallan_arknights.pt and magallan_arknights.safetensors, then use magallan_arknights.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use magallan_arknights.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

ÂêåÊó∂‰ΩøÁî®ÂÆÉ‰ª¨„ÄÇÂú®ËøôÁßçÊÉÖÂÜµ‰∏ãÔºåÊÇ®ÈúÄË¶Å‰∏ãËΩΩmagallan_arknights.ptÂíåmagallan_arknights.safetensorsËøô‰∏§‰∏™Êñá‰ª∂ÔºåÁÑ∂ÂêéÂ∞Ümagallan_arknights.ptÁî®‰ΩúÁ∫πÁêÜÂèçËΩ¨ÂµåÂÖ•Ôºå ÂêåÊó∂‰ΩøÁî®magallan_arknights.safetensors‰Ωú‰∏∫LoRA„ÄÇ

(Translated with ChatGPT)

The trigger word is magallan_arknights, and the recommended tags are best quality, masterpiece, highres, solo, {magallan_arknights:1.15}, multicolored_hair, streaked_hair, short_hair, white_hair, brown_hair, yellow_eyes, smile, jewelry, earrings, upper_body, bangs, hair_between_eyes.

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Magallan Arknights

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is adjusting the tags you are using.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/magallan_arknights, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/magallan_arknights, which may be helpful to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

Why Can't the Desired Character Outfits Be Accurately Generated

Our current training data is sourced from various image websites, and for a fully automated pipeline, it's challenging to accurately predict which official images a character possesses. Consequently, outfit generation relies on clustering based on labels from the training dataset in an attempt to achieve the best possible recreation. We will continue to address this issue and attempt optimization, but it remains a challenge that cannot be completely resolved. The accuracy of outfit recreation is also unlikely to match the level achieved by manually trained models.

In fact, this model's greatest strengths lie in recreating the inherent characteristics of the characters themselves and its relatively strong generalization capabilities, owing to its larger dataset. As such, this model is well-suited for tasks such as changing outfits, posing characters, and, of course, generating NSFW images of characters!üòâ".

For the following groups, it is not recommended to use this model and we express regret:

  1. Individuals who cannot tolerate any deviations from the original character design, even in the slightest detail.

  2. Individuals who are facing the application scenarios with high demands for accuracy in recreating character outfits.

  3. Individuals who cannot accept the potential randomness in AI-generated images based on the Stable Diffusion algorithm.

  4. Individuals who are not comfortable with the fully automated process of training character models using LoRA, or those who believe that training character models must be done purely through manual operations to avoid disrespecting the characters.

  5. Individuals who finds the generated image content offensive to their values.
